modules.description: This module manages user identities with functions to create and validate user IDs. It provides `v` and `v_exn` to construct user values from strings, ensuring valid format, and `id` to retrieve the underlying string identifier. It works with strings representing user IDs, such as "github:alice", and is used to handle authenticated user identities in web requests.

This module defines a set of roles used to represent different levels of access and permissions within a web interface. It includes functions for pretty-printing these roles in a human-readable format. Concrete use cases include role-based access control for user interfaces and logging or displaying user permissions in web applications.

This module defines a web site with role-based access control, handling user authentication and route authorization. It works with users, roles, and routes to secure web resources based on provided policies. Use it to build authenticated web interfaces where access to specific routes depends on user roles.

This module handles web request contexts, providing access to HTTP requests, CSRF tokens, and user authentication. It supports creating responses with HTML content, redirects, and errors, along with setting authenticated users via cookies. Use it to build web handlers that require session management, form handling, and templated responses.

This module implements a web interface with role-based access control, handling user authentication, route authorization, and request context management. It works with users represented as strings (e.g., "github:alice"), roles defining access levels, and routes secured via policies. Concrete use cases include building authenticated web applications with session management, CSRF protection, and role-based UI rendering.
